drama graduate student showcase the ballad of betsy paradise events at stanford drama graduate student showcase the ballad of betsy paradise facebook twitter email print add to calendar march 1 at 8pm & 10pm march 2 at 8pm & 10pm written by dan poston directed by joy brooke fairfield the ballad of betsy paradise is a play within a play within a dream of a play within a treehouse nestled in the towering redwood forest eleven year old jellia oceanblue was born and raised in northern california with as much opportunity as her mother could afford and grandmother could imagine but it's still not enough hungry for the exciting future of social revolution that she reads about on the internet jellia invites a flashy social theorist from new york city to stay in her treehouse for one event filled week but is the glamorous betsy paradise all that she seems with one eye turned to the past and one searching into the future this play looks at how generations construct and deconstruct each others myths and aspirations when thursday mar 1 2012 8 00 pm thursday mar 1 2012 10 00 pm friday mar 2 2012 8 00 pm friday mar 2 2012 10 00 pm where nitery theater in the old union map audience general public faculty staff students tags arts performance drama sponsor department of drama contact dramainfo stanford edu admission tickets $5 general admisssion at http drama stanford edu please note that this performance space does not accommodate late seating permalink http events stanford edu events 308 30863 more info last modified march 1 2012
